org.wattdepot.server

Class WattDepotPersistence

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wattdepot.server.WattDepotPersistence
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WattDepotPersistenceImpl

    public abstract class WattDepotPersistence
extends Object
    WattDepot persistence abstract interface. Different persistence implementations should subclass this class and implement their persistence schemes.
    Author:
    Cam Moore

      • defineCollectorProcessDefinition

        public abstract CollectorProcessDefinition defineCollectorProcessDefinition(String id,
                                                          String name,
                                                          String sensorId,
                                                          Long pollingInterval,
                                                          String depositoryId,
                                                          Set<Property> properties,
                                                          String orgId)
                                                                     throws UniqueIdException,
                                                                            MisMatchedOwnerException,
                                                                            IdNotFoundException,
                                                                            BadSlugException
        Defines a new CollectorProcessDefinition. This does not start any processes.
        Parameters:
        id - The unique id.
        name - The unique name.
        sensorId - The id of the Sensor to poll.
        pollingInterval - The polling interval.
        depositoryId - The id of the depository to use.
        properties - The properties associated with this CollectorProcessDefinition.
        orgId - the id of the owner of the CollectorProcessDefinition
        Returns:
        The defined CollectorProcessDefinition.
        Throws:
        UniqueIdException - if the id is already used for another CollectorProcessDefinintion.
        MisMatchedOwnerException - if the given owner doesn't match the owners of the Sensor or Depository.
        IdNotFoundException - if the sensorId or orgId are not defined.
        BadSlugException - if the given id isn't valid.
